Class MapAdapterEmptyTests

java.lang.Object
myTest.MapAdapterEmptyTests
public class MapAdapterEmptyTests extends Object
This test case tests the MapAdapter class in an empty state. Every method of the MapAdapter class is tested to ensure the class implementation is correct for empty maps. For each method tests are created to ensure correct behavior in normal and edge cases, including correct throw of exceptions and correct return values.
See Also:
  • MapAdapter
Design
This test case aims to verify the correct behavior of empty MapAdapter instances to ensure it correctly implements the HMap interface.
Libraries
JUnit 4.13, Hamcrest 1.3

    • testDefaultConstructor

      public void testDefaultConstructor()
      Tests that MapAdapter's default constructor creates a new empty map without exceptions.
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the default constructor creates an empty map by creating a new instance and checking if the map is empty.
      Description
      The instance created in the setUp() method is overwritten by a new one created by the default constructor of the MapAdapter. After creation the new instance is tested to be non-null and empty by asserting that MapAdapter.isEmpty() returns true on that instance and the same for the size.
      Preconditions
      None
      Postconditions
      The map is created and is empty
      Expected Results
      Map is created without exceptions, it's empty and has size 0.

    • testPutNewMapping

      public void testPutNewMapping()
      Tests that the MapAdapter.put(Object, Object) method adds a new mapping into the map.
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.put(Object, Object) method adds a valid mapping to the map.
      Description
      The MapAdapter.put(Object, Object) method is called with a valid key and a valid value on the empty map created by the setUp() method. For this test the inserted entry has the string "key" as key and "value" as value. The result is asserted to be null, as the key was not previously present in the map. After the null result is asserted, the map is checked to contain the new mapping by asserting that MapAdapter.get(Object) returns the value for the key "key". The map is also checked to be not empty after the put operation and the size is asserted to be 1.
      Preconditions
      The map is correctly instantiated
      Postconditions
      The map contains the new mapping
      Expected Results
      The MapAdapter.put(Object, Object) method adds a new mapping to the map, and the map is not empty after the put operation.

    • testPutAllNewMappings

      public void testPutAllNewMappings()
      Tests that the MapAdapter.putAll(Map) method adds new mappings from another map to the empty map.
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.putAll(Map) method adds new mappings from another map to the empty map.
      Description
      A new map is created with the MapAdapter default constructor then three mappings (for this test: "key1" -> "value1", "key2" -> "value2", "key3" -> "value3") are added to it. The MapAdapter.putAll(Map) method is then called with this new map as an argument. The map with the new mappings is then checked to contain the new mappings by asserting that all the values are correctly mapped to their respective keys, the map is not empty after the putAll operation and the size is asserted to be 3.
      Preconditions
      The map is correctly instantiated
      Postconditions
